I WANT MY MONEY BACK! I am not rating this on graphics that are old or other little quirks but the fact that I paid 6.99 for a game with laughable extras for a full version of this old game. There are no xtra collections ,morphing objects to find and I played the game twice trying to get the bonus chapter until I read it carefully and saw that the xtra bonus chapter is in the main game the little side trip to secret island is the bonus chapter was not enough to 6,99 plus tax!!!

Give me my money back now! I would have given a higher score because even though it's graphics are older I knew and didn't care. But there were no extra things to collect. Most important; I played the game all the way to end, l even watched the credits,had access to the mini games and H.O.s, yet I couldn't play the bonus game! The game acted like I hadn't played the main game.OVER PRICED 6.99 plus tax for a ancient game with the best of the extras not there or not working.SHAME ON YOU!üò•ü§î

GOOD GAME  I enjoyed this game, the graphics and storyline were good, the voices of the actors were fairly convincing so I could play with sound and the puzzles were okay,  but could have been a little more taxing for my taste.  The things that let it down were the length of the game it was very short and there was no bonus game, so value for money was very poor, and sometimes the hidden object scenes were poorly lit making it very difficult to see what the gs were.  However, there was an option to swap to mahjong so it was bearable.

I bought the third one at the same time as this so I'm going to play it next & hope it's much better.

Although this game visually was phenomenal it is like the devs forgot this was a game.  There was no continuity of the puzzles and it was almost impossible to tell if you got the right item you are looking for.   For instance in most games if you are missing some piece to unlock a door or such, the shape was obvious but this was not true for this.  Basically you spent most of the game running around blind using the hint button as a map.  Not my kind of fun.  Looks are not everything.
